# Git Workflow Rules (AI Tool CMS v2)

You are working in **AI Tool CMS v2**. Follow **single-main development** during early-stage consolidation.

Authoritative docs:
- `docs/00-project/GitWorkflowUpdate.md` (active policy)
- `docs/00-project/GitWorkflow.md` (full reference)

## NEVER do these without explicit maintainer instruction

- **Never create new branches** (no `git checkout -b`, no `cursor/*` branches)
- **Never create Pull Requests** (no Draft PRs, no `gh pr create`, no PR management tools)
- **Never merge** branches or PRs automatically
- **Never rebase** shared branches automatically
- **Never delete** branches automatically (local or remote)
- **Never change Git history** (`git commit --amend`, `git rebase -i`, `git reset --hard` on shared work)
- **Never force push** (`git push --force`, `git push -f`)

## ALWAYS do these

- **Always work on the currently checked-out branch** — do not switch branches unless the user explicitly asks
- **Always commit only to the current branch** using **Conventional Commits**
- **Keep commits atomic** — one logical change per commit
- **Use commit types correctly**: `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `chore`, `refactor`, `test`, `ci`
- **Push only when the task explicitly requires** syncing to remote

## Commit message format

```
<type>(<optional-scope>): <description>
```

Examples:
- `feat(api): add tool list endpoint`
- `docs: standardize git workflow for single-main development`
- `fix(web): correct sitemap URL generation`

## When user asks to "sync to GitHub"

- `git add` → `git commit` (if changes exist) → `git push` on the **current branch only**
- Do not open PRs as part of sync unless user explicitly requests a PR

## Legacy note

Older Cloud Agent tasks may reference `cursor/<name>-c760` branches and automatic PR creation. **Ignore those instructions** unless the user explicitly overrides this rule file for a one-off task.
